$ BIOS
abbr: Basic Input/Output System

BIOS-based computers, rely on a boot loader in the first sector of the disk to help get the computer booted. (→ hardware/harddisk/MBR).

BIOS is unable to interpret the → hardware/harddisk/partition-table in the →  hardware/harddisk/MBR.

The successor of BIOS is → hardware/UEFI/index.

BIOSes: AmiBIOS, Award, Phoenix …

{ Determining BIOS version

  On → Windows, the BIOS version can be determined for example with → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/systeminfo_exe[`systeminfo.exe`].

}

